<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="595" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1889,2021]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,428]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="595" pageId="1" pageNumber="594">
<taxonomicName authority="Edwards" authorityName="Edwards" box="[151,425,1889,1913]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Proceroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,309,1889,1913]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="594">Proceroplatus</emphasis>
Edwards
</taxonomicName>
is comprised of about 
<number box="[734,762,1889,1913]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" value="38.0">38</number>
named species (
<bibRefCitation author="Evenhuis" box="[978,1177,1889,1913]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" refString="Evenhuis, N. L. (2006 b) Catalog of the Keroplatidae of the world. Bishop Museum Bulletin in Entomology, 13, 1 - 177." type="journal article" year="2006" yearSuffix="b">
Evenhuis 
<number box="[1102,1162,1889,1913]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" value="2006.0">2006</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
). The genus is pancircumtropical with the vast majority of the species being found in the Neotropical region. Using the keys in 
<bibRefCitation author="Edwards" box="[151,333,1961,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" refString="Edwards, F. W. (1929) Notes on the Ceroplatinae, with descriptions of new Australian species (Diptera, Mycetophilidae). Proceedings of the Linnaean Society of New South Wales, 54 (3), 162 - 175." type="journal article" year="1929">
Edwards (
<number box="[266,325,1961,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" value="1929.0">1929</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Lane" box="[393,535,1961,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" refString="Lane, J. (1950) Neotropical Ceroplatinae (Diptera, Mycetophilidae). Dusenia, 1, 32 - 69." type="journal article" year="1950">
Lane (
<number box="[466,526,1961,1985]" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" value="1950.0">1950</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, this specimen keys to 
<taxonomicName box="[807,965,1961,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Proceroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="594" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[807,965,1961,1985]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="594">Proceroplatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The described species are characterized primarily by thoracic setation (laterotergite and anepisternum pilose, mesonotum uniformly setulose, and meron bare) and with patterning in the wing, but species in the genus have a diverse array of shapes in the male genitalia, especially the gonostyli. Revisionary work is obviously in need to determine generic boundaries and correct species placement. The amber fossil species described in this work has gonostyli (thin, uniramous) that are quite different from most species in the genus (thicker and biramous or with a mesal denticle/tooth or long mesal process), but it fits the current generic concepts in the other salient characters given above. 
<bibRefCitation author="Matile" box="[1219,1436,295,319]" pageId="2" pageNumber="595" refString="Matile, L. (1982) Systematique, phylogenie et biogeographie des dipteres Keroplatidae des Petites Antilles et de Trinidad. Bulletin du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle (A), 4 (1 - 2), 189 - 235." type="journal article" year="1982">
Matile (
<number box="[1310,1371,295,319]" pageId="2" pageNumber="595" value="1982.0">1982</number>
: 
<number box="[1385,1428,295,319]" pageId="2" pageNumber="595" value="217.0">217</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned an undescribed species with simple gonostyli from 
<collectingCountry box="[849,903,333,356]" name="Peru" pageId="2" pageNumber="595">Peru</collectingCountry>
, so the variation in genitalic characters noted in the fossil species described here is within the range of variation within the genus as currently known. It is thus placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[260,418,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Proceroplatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[260,418,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="595">Proceroplatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
pending future revisionary studies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
